{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775878513423,"sessionID":"ses_285647e18ffeoctb678uOjeElq","part":{"id":"prt_d7a9b9d19001sVtDbxeRpBr9Mt","messageID":"msg_d7a9b944e001FqfL6J9581DypN","sessionID":"ses_285647e18ffeoctb678uOjeElq","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_743d4b392bc44f9b8bb36720","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-034/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-034/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-034: CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 workflows) — Delta Spec\n2: \n3: ## Context\n4: \n5: - **Module:** `.github`\n6: - **Language:** YAML\n7: - **Size:** L\n8: - **Base specs:** (No directly matching specs)\n9: \n10: ## Scope\n11: \n12: <!-- TODO: Describe the scope of this delta spec -->\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## File Changes\n17: \n18: | Action | File | Description |\n19: |--------|------|-------------|\n20: | <!-- TODO --> | <!-- TODO --> | <!-- TODO --> |\n\n(End of file - total 20 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-034: CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 workflows) — Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** `.github`\n- **Language:** YAML\n- **Size:** L\n- **Base specs:** (No directly matching specs)\n\n## Scope\n\n<!-- TODO: Describe the scope of this delta spec -->\n\n---\n\n## File Changes\n\n| Action | File | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| <!-- TODO --> | <!-- TODO --> | <!-- TODO --> |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-034/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775878513410,"end":1775878513421}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775878515456,"sessionID":"ses_285647e18ffeoctb678uOjeElq","part":{"id":"prt_d7a9ba736001ZcRhisynJwzFo7","messageID":"msg_d7a9b944e001FqfL6J9581DypN","sessionID":"ses_285647e18ffeoctb678uOjeElq","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_a5fc1dd9d2874c1494bd96b1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/ci-cd/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/ci-cd/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # CI/CD Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: Automate validation on pull requests (build, lint, tests, codegen drift checks), publish container images on pushes to `main` and version tags, run end-to-end tests on Kind, exercise the Python SDK, and enforce spelling and copyright consistency.\n5: \n6: ## Requirements\n7: \n8: ### Requirement: Pull request build verification\n9: The system SHALL build the Workload Manager Docker image on pull requests targeting `main` or `release-*` branches.\n10: \n11: #### Scenario: Docker build in CI\n12: - **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*`\n13: - **WHEN** the “Agentcube CI Workflow” job runs\n14: - **THEN** it SHALL checkout the repository, set up Docker Buildx, verify `docker`/`buildx` versions, and run `make docker-build`\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: Go lint on changed Go code\n17: The system SHALL run `make lint` (golangci-lint) when Go-related paths change on pull requests to `main` or `release-*`.\n18: \n19: #### Scenario: Path-filtered lint\n20: - **GIVEN** a pull request and path filter matches `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, or `.github/workflows/lint.yml`\n21: - **WHEN** the Lint workflow runs\n22: - **THEN** it SHALL use Go `1.24` and execute `make lint`\n23: \n24: ### Requirement: Code generation check\n25: The system SHALL verify generated artifacts match `make gen-all` when API, hack, workflow, or Makefile inputs change.\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Regenerate and diff\n28: - **GIVEN** path filter matches `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, or `Makefile`\n29: - **WHEN** the Codegen Check workflow runs with Go `1.24.4`\n30: - **THEN** it SHALL run `make gen-check` (which runs `gen-all` and `git diff --exit-code`)\n31: \n32: ### Requirement: Go test coverage reporting\n33: The system SHALL run race-enabled coverage tests on `pkg/...` for qualifying pull requests and merge groups, optionally uploading to Codecov.\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Coverage command\n36: - **GIVEN** path filter `coverage` matches (broad glob excluding some media/docs per workflow)\n37: - **WHEN** the Test Coverage job runs with Go `1.24`\n38: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `go test -race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/... ./pkg/...` and upload `coverage.out` as an artifact\n39: \n40: ### Requirement: E2E testing on Kind\n41: The system SHALL run `make e2e` in CI using a Kind-capable Ubuntu runner, capturing logs on failure.\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: E2E job lifecycle\n44: - **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*`\n45: - **WHEN** the E2E workflow runs\n46: - **THEN** it SHALL set `ARTIFACTS_PATH=${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`, install Kind tool `v0.30.0` (`install_only: true`), run `make e2e` with Go `1.23`, upload `e2e-logs` on failure, and always run `make e2e-clean`\n47: \n48: ### Requirement: Python SDK unit tests\n49: The system SHALL run pytest for the SDK when `sdk-python/**` changes.\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: Editable install and pytest\n52: - **GIVEN** path filter matches `sdk-python/**`\n53: - **WHEN** the Python SDK Tests job runs with Python `3.12` in `sdk-python/`\n54: - **THEN** it SHALL `pip install pytest`, `pip install -e .`, and run `python -m pytest tests/ -v`\n55: \n56: ### Requirement: Python lint\n57: The system SHALL run Ruff from repository root using `pyproject.toml` when Python-touching paths change.\n58: \n59: #### Scenario: Ruff check\n60: - **GIVEN** path filter matches `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py`, `pyproject.toml`, or the workflow file\n61: - **WHEN** the Python Lint job runs with Python `3.10`\n62: - **THEN** it SHALL `pip install ruff` and run `python3 -m ruff check . --config pyproject.toml`\n63: \n64: ### Requirement: Spelling check (codespell)\n65: The system SHALL run codespell on the repository for pull requests to `main` or `release-*`, temporarily moving files that cause false positives.\n66: \n67: #### Scenario: Codespell invocation\n68: - **GIVEN** checkout complete\n69: - **WHEN** codespell runs after backup/remove of `pyproject.toml`, `package-lock.json`, `package.json` at repo root (and nested copies per `find`)\n70: - **THEN** it SHALL use `pip install codespell` and run codespell with `--check-filenames`, specified `--skip` globs, and `--ignore-words-list fo,nam,te,notin,NotIn` on `.`, then restore backed-up files\n71: \n72: ### Requirement: Copyright header check\n73: The system SHALL ensure `make gen-copyright` produces no git diff when applicable files change.\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: Copyright workflow\n76: - **GIVEN** path filter marks `copyright` (all paths minus exclusions for md/svg/png/docs/.github per workflow)\n77: - **WHEN** the job runs\n78: - **THEN** it SHALL install `moreutils` (`sponge`), run `make gen-copyright`, and `git diff --exit-code`\n79: \n80: ### Requirement: Release image publication\n81: The system SHALL build and push multi-architecture images for workloadmanager, router, and picod to GitHub Container Registry on pushes to `main` and on semantic version tags.\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: Tag selects image tag\n84: - **GIVEN** a `push` event\n85: - **WHEN** `github.ref_type` is `tag`, environment `TAG` SHALL be `github.ref_name`; otherwise `TAG` SHALL be `latest`\n86: - **THEN** the job SHALL log in to `ghcr.io` with `GITHUB_TOKEN` and run `make docker-buildx-push*`, setting `IMAGE_REGISTRY=ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}` and per-image `*_IMAGE=<name>:${TAG}`\n87: \n88: ### Requirement: Workflow approval for first-time contributors\n89: The system SHALL optionally approve pending workflow runs for pull requests from repeat contributors or those labeled `ok-to-test`.\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: Approve action_required runs\n92: - **GIVEN** `pull_request_target` on `main` or `release-**` with label/sync events\n93: - **WHEN** the contributor is not first-time (more than one PR) or PR has `ok-to-test`\n94: - **THEN** the workflow SHALL list workflow runs for the head SHA with `status: action_required` and call `approveWorkflowRun` for each\n\n(End of file - total 94 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# CI/CD Specification\n\n## Purpose\nAutomate validation on pull requests (build, lint, tests, codegen drift checks), publish container images on pushes to `main` and version tags, run end-to-end tests on Kind, exercise the Python SDK, and enforce spelling and copyright consistency.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Pull request build verification\nThe system SHALL build the Workload Manager Docker image on pull requests targeting `main` or `release-*` branches.\n\n#### Scenario: Docker build in CI\n- **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*`\n- **WHEN** the “Agentcube CI Workflow” job runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL checkout the repository, set up Docker Buildx, verify `docker`/`buildx` versions, and run `make docker-build`\n\n### Requirement: Go lint on changed Go code\nThe system SHALL run `make lint` (golangci-lint) when Go-related paths change on pull requests to `main` or `release-*`.\n\n#### Scenario: Path-filtered lint\n- **GIVEN** a pull request and path filter matches `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, or `.github/workflows/lint.yml`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/ci-cd/spec.md","time":{"start":1775878515448,"end":1775878515455}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775878516687,"sessionID":"ses_285647e18ffeoctb678uOjeElq","part":{"id":"prt_d7a9bab75001k7Sd2QSd4sw5Qj","messageID":"msg_d7a9b944e001FqfL6J9581DypN","sessionID":"ses_285647e18ffeoctb678uOjeElq","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_8d23857b2d1a4174affc8f3e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-033/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-033/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-033: Makefile 构建目标体系 — Delta Spec\n2: \n3: ## Context\n4: \n5: - **Module:** `root`\n6: - **Language:** Makefile\n7: - **Size:** M\n8: - **Base specs:** (No directly matching specs)\n9: \n10: ## Scope\n11: \n12: This delta spec covers the creation of a root-level `Makefile` for the AgentCube project, providing a unified entry point for building Go binaries, Docker images, running tests, linting, and Helm operations. The Makefile SHALL orchestrate existing tooling (go, docker, helm, golangci-lint) without modifying any existing source code, Dockerfiles, or Helm charts.\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## Variables and Configuration\n17: \n18: ### Requirement: Default variable values\n19: The Makefile SHALL define the following variables with default values that can be overridden by the caller:\n20: \n21: | Variable | Default | Description |\n22: |----------|---------|-------------|\n23: | `TAG` | `latest` | Docker image tag |\n24: | `REGISTRY` | `agentcube` | Docker image registry prefix |\n25: | `GOOS` | `$(shell go env GOOS)` | Target operating system |\n26: | `GOARCH` | `$(shell go env GOARCH)` | Target architecture |\n27: | `BIN_DIR` | `bin` | Binary output directory |\n28: | `LDFLAGS` | `-s -w` | Linker flags (strip debug + compress) |\n29: | `VERBOSE` | (empty) | Set to `1` to enable verbose command output |\n30: \n31: #### Scenario: TAG override\n32: - **GIVEN** the Makefile is invoked with `make docker TAG=v0.1.0`\n33: - **WHEN** Docker images are built\n34: - **THEN** the image tag SHALL be `v0.1.0` instead of `latest`\n35: \n36: #### Scenario: REGISTRY override\n37: - **GIVEN** the Makefile is invoked with `make docker REGISTRY=myregistry.io/agentcube`\n38: - **WHEN** Docker images are built\n39: - **THEN** image names SHALL be prefixed with `myregistry.io/agentcube/`\n40: \n41: #### Scenario: Cross-compilation via GOOS/GOARCH\n42: - **GIVEN** the Makefile is invoked with `make build GOOS=linux GOARCH=arm64`\n43: - **WHEN** Go binaries are compiled\n44: - **THEN** `GOOS=linux` and `GOARCH=arm64` SHALL be passed to `go build`\n45: \n46: #### Scenario: VERBOSE enables command echo\n47: - **GIVEN** `VERBOSE=1` is set\n48: - **WHEN** any target executes\n49: - **THEN** the underlying commands SHALL be printed before execution\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: VERBOSE=0 suppresses command echo\n52: - **GIVEN** `VERBOSE` is not set or is empty\n53: - **WHEN** any target executes\n54: - **THEN** the underlying commands SHALL NOT be printed (silent by default)\n55: \n56: ---\n57: \n58: ## Go Build Targets\n59: \n60: ### Requirement: build\n61: The Makefile SHALL provide a `build` target that compiles all Go binaries to `$(BIN_DIR)/`. The binaries SHALL be: `router`, `workloadmanager`, `agentd`, `picod`.\n62: \n63: #### Scenario: build compiles all binaries\n64: - **GIVEN** the project root contains `cmd/router/`, `cmd/workloadmanager/`, `cmd/agentd/`, `cmd/picod/`\n65: - **WHEN** `make build` is executed\n66: - **THEN** `$(BIN_DIR)/router`, `$(BIN_DIR)/workloadmanager`, `$(BIN_DIR)/agentd`, and `$(BIN_DIR)/picod` SHALL exist as executable files\n67: \n68: #### Scenario: build uses LDFLAGS\n69: - **GIVEN** `LDFLAGS` is set to `-s -w`\n70: - **WHEN** `make build` is executed\n71: - **THEN** `go build` SHALL be invoked with `-ldflags '-s -w'`\n72: \n73: #### Scenario: build applies GOOS/GOARCH\n74: - **GIVEN** `make build GOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64` is executed\n75: - **WHEN** the binaries are compiled\n76: - **THEN** all output binaries SHALL be built for `linux/amd64`\n77: \n78: ### Requirement: build/<binary>\n79: The Makefile SHALL provide per-binary build targets in the form `build/<binary>` for each of: `router`, `workloadmanager`, `agentd`, `picod`.\n80: \n81: #### Scenario: build/router compiles only router\n82: - **GIVEN** `make build/router` is executed\n83: - **WHEN** the build completes\n84: - **THEN** `$(BIN_DIR)/router` SHALL exist\n85: - **AND** `$(BIN_DIR)/workloadmanager`, `$(BIN_DIR)/agentd`, `$(BIN_DIR)/picod` SHALL NOT be created by this invocation\n86: \n87: #### Scenario: build/picod compiles only picod\n88: - **GIVEN** `make build/picod` is executed\n89: - **WHEN** the build completes\n90: - **THEN** `$(BIN_DIR)/picod` SHALL exist\n91: \n92: #### Scenario: build/<binary> uses correct package path\n93: - **GIVEN** `make build/router` is executed\n94: - **WHEN** the build command is inspected\n95: - **THEN** it SHALL compile `./cmd/router` (not `./cmd/` or any other path)\n96: \n97: ### Requirement: clean\n98: The Makefile SHALL provide a `clean` target that removes the `$(BIN_DIR)/` directory and all build artifacts.\n99: \n100: #### Scenario: clean removes bin directory\n101: - **GIVEN** `make build` has been run and `$(BIN_DIR)/` exists with binaries\n102: - **WHEN** `make clean` is executed\n103: - **THEN** the `$(BIN_DIR)/` directory SHALL be removed\n104: \n105: #### Scenario: clean is idempotent\n106: - **GIVEN** `$(BIN_DIR)/` does not exist\n107: - **WHEN** `make clean` is executed\n108: - **THEN** the command SHALL succeed without error\n109: \n110: ---\n111: \n112: ## Docker Build Targets\n113: \n114: ### Requirement: docker\n115: The Makefile SHALL provide a `docker` target that builds all Docker images: `agentcube` (from `docker/Dockerfile`), `router` (from `docker/Dockerfile.router`), and `picod` (from `docker/Dockerfile.picod`).\n116: \n117: #### Scenario: docker builds all images\n118: - **GIVEN** `make docker TAG=latest REGISTRY=agentcube` is executed\n119: - **WHEN** the build completes\n120: - **THEN** the following images SHALL exist in the local Docker daemon:\n121:   - `agentcube/agentcube:latest`\n122:   - `agentcube/router:latest`\n123:   - `agentcube/picod:latest`\n124: \n125: #### Scenario: docker uses correct Dockerfiles\n126: - **GIVEN** `make docker` is executed\n127: - **WHEN** the docker build commands are inspected\n128: - **THEN** the agentcube image SHALL use `-f docker/Dockerfile`, router SHALL use `-f docker/Dockerfile.router`, and picod SHALL use `-f docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n129: \n130: #### Scenario: docker applies TAG variable\n131: - **GIVEN** `make docker TAG=v0.2.0` is executed\n132: - **WHEN** the build completes\n133: - **THEN** all images SHALL be tagged with `v0.2.0` (e.g., `agentcube/agentcube:v0.2.0`)\n134: \n135: #### Scenario: docker applies REGISTRY variable\n136: - **GIVEN** `make docker REGISTRY=ghcr.io/myorg` is executed\n137: - **WHEN** the build completes\n138: - **THEN** image names SHALL be prefixed with `ghcr.io/myorg/` (e.g., `ghcr.io/myorg/router:latest`)\n139: \n140: ### Requirement: docker/<image>\n141: The Makefile SHALL provide per-image build targets in the form `docker/<image>` for each of: `agentcube`, `router`, `picod`.\n142: \n143: #### Scenario: docker/router builds only router image\n144: - **GIVEN** `make docker/router TAG=latest` is executed\n145: - **WHEN** the build completes\n146: - **THEN** `agentcube/router:latest` SHALL exist in the local Docker daemon\n147: - **AND** `agentcube/agentcube:latest` and `agentcube/picod:latest` SHALL NOT be built by this invocation\n148: \n149: #### Scenario: docker/picod uses correct Dockerfile\n150: - **GIVEN** `make docker/picod` is executed\n151: - **WHEN** the docker build command is inspected\n152: - **THEN** it SHALL use `-f docker/Dockerfile.picod` with the project root as build context\n153: \n154: ---\n155: \n156: ## Test Targets\n157: \n158: ### Requirement: test\n159: The Makefile SHALL provide a `test` target that runs all Go unit tests.\n160: \n161: #### Scenario: test runs all Go tests\n162: - **GIVEN** `make test` is executed\n163: - **WHEN** the command completes\n164: - **THEN** `go test ./...` SHALL have been executed\n165: - **AND** the exit code SHALL reflect test pass/fail (non-zero on failure)\n166: \n167: ### Requirement: test-coverage\n168: The Makefile SHALL provide a `test-coverage` target that runs Go tests with coverage profiling and writes the output to `coverage.out`.\n169: \n170: #### Scenario: test-coverage generates coverage report\n171: - **GIVEN** `make test-coverage` is executed\n172: - **WHEN** the command completes\n173: - **THEN** `coverage.out` SHALL exist in the project root\n174: - **AND** the file SHALL contain valid Go coverage data (parseable by `go tool cover`)\n175: \n176: #### Scenario: test-coverage covers all packages\n177: - **GIVEN** `make test-coverage` is executed\n178: - **WHEN** the command is inspected\n179: - **THEN** it SHALL include `-coverprofile=coverage.out` flag\n180: \n181: ### Requirement: test-chart\n182: The Makefile SHALL provide a `test-chart` target that runs the Helm chart render test script.\n183: \n184: #### Scenario: test-chart executes render script\n185: - **GIVEN** `make test-chart` is executed\n186: - **WHEN** the command completes\n187: - **THEN** `bash test/chart/test_render.sh` SHALL have been executed\n188: - **AND** the exit code SHALL reflect the script's pass/fail status\n189: \n190: ---\n191: \n192: ## Code Quality Targets\n193: \n194: ### Requirement: lint\n195: The Makefile SHALL provide a `lint` target that runs `golangci-lint`.\n196: \n197: #### Scenario: lint runs golangci-lint\n198: - **GIVEN** `make lint` is executed\n199: - **WHEN** the command completes\n200: - **THEN** `golangci-lint run` SHALL have been executed\n201: - **AND** the exit code SHALL be non-zero if lint violations are found\n202: \n203: ### Requirement: fmt\n204: The Makefile SHALL provide a `fmt` target that formats Go source code.\n205: \n206: #### Scenario: fmt formats all Go files\n207: - **GIVEN** `make fmt` is executed\n208: - **WHEN** the command completes\n209: - **THEN** `go fmt ./...` SHALL have been executed\n210: - **AND** any unformatted Go files SHALL be reformatted in place\n211: \n212: ### Requirement: vet\n213: The Makefile SHALL provide a `vet` target that runs Go's static analyzer.\n214: \n215: #### Scenario: vet runs go vet\n216: - **GIVEN** `make vet` is executed\n217: - **WHEN** the command completes\n218: - **THEN** `go vet ./...` SHALL have been executed\n219: - **AND** the exit code SHALL be non-zero if vet issues are found\n220: \n221: ---\n222: \n223: ## Helm Targets\n224: \n225: ### Requirement: helm-lint\n226: The Makefile SHALL provide a `helm-lint` target that validates Helm charts.\n227: \n228: #### Scenario: helm-lint validates charts\n229: - **GIVEN** `make helm-lint` is executed\n230: - **WHEN** the command completes\n231: - **THEN** `helm lint manifests/` (or the appropriate chart path) SHALL have been executed\n232: - **AND** the exit code SHALL reflect lint pass/fail\n233: \n234: ### Requirement: helm-template\n235: The Makefile SHALL provide a `helm-template` target that renders Helm templates for inspection.\n236: \n237: #### Scenario: helm-template outputs rendered manifests\n238: - **GIVEN** `make helm-template` is executed\n239: - **WHEN** the command completes\n240: - **THEN** `helm template` SHALL output the rendered Kubernetes manifests to stdout\n241: - **AND** the command SHALL NOT modify any files (read-only operation)\n242: \n243: ---\n244: \n245: ## Python Targets\n246: \n247: ### Requirement: python-lint\n248: The Makefile SHALL provide a `python-lint` target that runs Python linting tools against the SDK/CLI code, gracefully handling the case where tools are not installed.\n249: \n250: #### Scenario: python-lint runs ruff when available\n251: - **GIVEN** `ruff` is installed and `make python-lint` is executed\n252: - **WHEN** the command completes\n253: - **THEN** `ruff check` (or equivalent) SHALL have been run against the Python SDK/CLI source\n254: \n255: #### Scenario: python-lint succeeds when tools are absent\n256: - **GIVEN** neither `ruff` nor `flake8` is installed and `make python-lint` is executed\n257: - **WHEN** the command completes\n258: - **THEN** the target SHALL succeed (exit 0) with a warning message indicating no lint tool was found\n259: \n260: ### Requirement: python-test\n261: The Makefile SHALL provide a `python-test` target that runs Python tests, gracefully handling the case where pytest is not installed.\n262: \n263: #### Scenario: python-test runs pytest when available\n264: - **GIVEN** `pytest` is installed and `make python-test` is executed\n265: - **WHEN** the command completes\n266: - **THEN** `pytest` SHALL have been run against the Python SDK/CLI test directory\n267: \n268: #### Scenario: python-test succeeds when pytest is absent\n269: - **GIVEN** `pytest` is not installed and `make python-test` is executed\n270: - **WHEN** the command completes\n271: - **THEN** the target SHALL succeed (exit 0) with a warning message indicating pytest was not found\n272: \n273: ---\n274: \n275: ## Composite Targets\n276: \n277: ### Requirement: all\n278: The Makefile SHALL provide an `all` target that serves as the default target and runs a complete local development verification.\n279: \n280: #### Scenario: all runs build, test, and lint\n281: - **GIVEN** `make` (or `make all`) is executed with no arguments\n282: - **WHEN** the command completes\n283: - **THEN** `make build`, `make test`, and `make lint` SHALL all have been executed\n284: - **AND** execution SHALL stop on the first failure (non-zero exit code)\n285: \n286: ### Requirement: ci\n287: The Makefile SHALL provide a `ci` target that runs the full CI gate verification suite.\n288: \n289: #### Scenario: ci runs full CI gate\n290: - **GIVEN** `make ci` is executed\n291: - **WHEN** the command completes\n292: - **THEN** `make build`, `make test`, `make test-coverage`, `make lint`, and `make helm-lint` SHALL all have been executed\n293: - **AND** execution SHALL stop on the first failure\n294: \n295: #### Scenario: ci produces coverage output\n296: - **GIVEN** `make ci` is executed\n297: - **WHEN** the command completes successfully\n298: - **THEN** `coverage.out` SHALL exist in the project root\n299: \n300: ---\n301: \n302: ## Phony Targets\n303: \n304: ### Requirement: .PHONY declaration\n305: All non-file-producing targets SHALL be declared as `.PHONY` to prevent conflicts with files of the same name.\n306: \n307: #### Scenario: all targets are phony\n308: - **GIVEN** the Makefile is parsed\n309: - **WHEN** `.PHONY` declarations are inspected\n310: - **THEN** the following targets SHALL be declared `.PHONY`:\n311:   `all`, `build`, `clean`, `test`, `test-coverage`, `test-chart`, `lint`, `fmt`, `vet`,\n312:   `docker`, `helm-lint`, `helm-template`, `python-lint`, `python-test`, `ci`,\n313:   and all `build/<binary>` and `docker/<image>` targets\n314: \n315: #### Scenario: phony targets work even if同名 files exist\n316: - **GIVEN** a file named `build` exists in the project root\n317: - **WHEN** `make build` is executed\n318: - **THEN** the Makefile target SHALL execute (not treat `build` as a file dependency)\n319: \n320: ---\n321: \n322: ## Error Handling\n323: \n324: ### Requirement: Build failure propagation\n325: When any sub-command in a target fails, the Makefile SHALL propagate the non-zero exit code.\n326: \n327: #### Scenario: go build failure stops build\n328: - **GIVEN** a Go source file contains a compilation error\n329: - **WHEN** `make build` is executed\n330: - **THEN** the command SHALL exit with a non-zero status\n331: - **AND** no further binaries SHALL be built after the failure\n332: \n333: #### Scenario: test failure stops ci\n334: - **GIVEN** a Go test is failing\n335: - **WHEN** `make ci` is executed\n336: - **THEN** the command SHALL exit with a non-zero status after `make test` fails\n337: - **AND** `make lint` and `make helm-lint` SHALL NOT be executed\n338: \n339: ### Requirement: Missing tool graceful handling\n340: Targets that depend on external tools (golangci-lint, helm, ruff, pytest) SHALL fail with a clear error message when the tool is not found, except for Python targets which SHALL warn and succeed.\n341: \n342: #### Scenario: golangci-lint missing causes lint failure\n343: - **GIVEN** `golangci-lint` is not installed\n344: - **WHEN** `make lint` is executed\n345: - **THEN** the command SHALL fail with a message indicating `golangci-lint` is required\n346: \n347: #### Scenario: helm missing causes helm-lint failure\n348: - **GIVEN** `helm` is not installed\n349: - **WHEN** `make helm-lint` is executed\n350: - **THEN** the command SHALL fail with a message indicating `helm` is required\n351: \n352: ---\n353: \n354: ## File Changes\n355: \n356: | Action | File | Description |\n357: |--------|------|-------------|\n358: | Create | `Makefile` | Root-level Makefile with all build, test, docker, lint, helm, and python targets |\n\n(End of file - total 358 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-033: Makefile 构建目标体系 — Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** `root`\n- **Language:** Makefile\n- **Size:** M\n- **Base specs:** (No directly matching specs)\n\n## Scope\n\nThis delta spec covers the creation of a root-level `Makefile` for the AgentCube project, providing a unified entry point for building Go binaries, Docker images, running tests, linting, and Helm operations. The Makefile SHALL orchestrate existing tooling (go, docker, helm, golangci-lint) without modifying any existing source code, Dockerfiles, or Helm charts.\n\n---\n\n## Variables and Configuration\n\n### Requirement: Default variable values\nThe Makefile SHALL define the following variables with default values that can be overridden by the caller:\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-033/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775878516675,"end":1775878516684}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775878517753,"sessionID":"ses_285647e18ffeoctb678uOjeElq","part":{"id":"prt_d7a9bb02c001j9bRF6rLTzFM2o","messageID":"msg_d7a9b944e001FqfL6J9581DypN","sessionID":"ses_285647e18ffeoctb678uOjeElq","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_4350cc5cd8414a99ac6b4497","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-032/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-032/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-032: Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (3 images) — Delta Spec\n2: \n3: ## Context\n4: \n5: - **Module:** `docker`\n6: - **Language:** Dockerfile\n7: - **Size:** S\n8: - **Base specs:** `deployment/spec.md` (Requirement: Docker images for core binaries)\n9: \n10: ## Delta Requirements\n11: \n12: ### Requirement: Workload Manager Dockerfile (multi-stage)\n13: \n14: The system SHALL provide `docker/Dockerfile` that builds the Workload Manager binary via a multi-stage Docker build: a Go builder stage compiles `cmd/workloadmanager` with `CGO_ENABLED=0`, and a minimal runtime stage copies the binary into an Alpine 3.19 image running as non-root user `apiserver` (UID 1000), exposing port 8080.\n15: \n16: #### Scenario: Builder stage uses Go toolchain\n17: - **GIVEN** `docker/Dockerfile` is invoked with the repository root as build context\n18: - **WHEN** the first (builder) stage is evaluated\n19: - **THEN** it SHALL use a Go base image (e.g. `golang:1.25-alpine`) and set `CGO_ENABLED=0` in the build environment\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Builder stage compiles workloadmanager binary\n22: - **GIVEN** the builder stage has the repository source available\n23: - **WHEN** `go build` runs\n24: - **THEN** it SHALL compile `./cmd/workloadmanager` and produce a static Linux binary at `/workloadmanager` (or equivalent output path)\n25: \n26: #### Scenario: Runtime stage uses Alpine 3.19\n27: - **GIVEN** the second (runtime) stage in `docker/Dockerfile`\n28: - **WHEN** the base image is inspected\n29: - **THEN** it SHALL be `alpine:3.19` (or a digest-pinned equivalent)\n30: \n31: #### Scenario: Binary is copied from builder to runtime\n32: - **GIVEN** both stages exist in `docker/Dockerfile`\n33: - **WHEN** the `COPY --from=builder` instruction is evaluated\n34: - **THEN** it SHALL copy the compiled `workloadmanager` binary from the builder stage into the runtime image\n35: \n36: #### Scenario: Non-root user apiserver is created\n37: - **GIVEN** the runtime stage\n38: - **WHEN** the image is built\n39: - **THEN** it SHALL create a user `apiserver` with UID 1000 and set `USER apiserver` as the active user\n40: \n41: #### Scenario: Port 8080 is exposed\n42: - **GIVEN** the runtime stage\n43: - **WHEN** the image metadata is inspected\n44: - **THEN** `EXPOSE 8080` SHALL be present\n45: \n46: #### Scenario: Entrypoint runs the workloadmanager binary\n47: - **GIVEN** a container launched from the built image\n48: - **WHEN** the container starts\n49: - **THEN** it SHALL execute the `workloadmanager` binary (via `ENTRYPOINT` or `CMD`)\n50: \n51: ### Requirement: Router Dockerfile (multi-stage)\n52: \n53: The system SHALL provide `docker/Dockerfile.router` that builds the Router binary via a multi-stage Docker build: a Go builder stage compiles `cmd/router` with `CGO_ENABLED=0`, and a minimal runtime stage copies the binary into an Alpine 3.19 image running as non-root user `router` (UID 1000), exposing port 8080.\n54: \n55: #### Scenario: Builder stage compiles router binary\n56: - **GIVEN** `docker/Dockerfile.router` is invoked with the repository root as build context\n57: - **WHEN** the builder stage runs `go build`\n58: - **THEN** it SHALL compile `./cmd/router` with `CGO_ENABLED=0` and produce a static Linux binary\n59: \n60: #### Scenario: Runtime stage uses Alpine 3.19\n61: - **GIVEN** the runtime stage in `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n62: - **WHEN** the base image is inspected\n63: - **THEN** it SHALL be `alpine:3.19` (or a digest-pinned equivalent)\n64: \n65: #### Scenario: Non-root user router is created\n66: - **GIVEN** the runtime stage\n67: - **WHEN** the image is built\n68: - **THEN** it SHALL create a user `router` with UID 1000 and set `USER router` as the active user\n69: \n70: #### Scenario: Port 8080 is exposed\n71: - **GIVEN** the runtime stage\n72: - **WHEN** the image metadata is inspected\n73: - **THEN** `EXPOSE 8080` SHALL be present\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: Entrypoint runs the router binary\n76: - **GIVEN** a container launched from the built image\n77: - **WHEN** the container starts\n78: - **THEN** it SHALL execute the `router` binary (via `ENTRYPOINT` or `CMD`)\n79: \n80: ### Requirement: PicoD Dockerfile (multi-stage)\n81: \n82: The system SHALL provide `docker/Dockerfile.picod` that builds the PicoD daemon binary via a multi-stage Docker build: a Go builder stage compiles `cmd/picod` with `CGO_ENABLED=0`, and a minimal runtime stage copies the binary into an Alpine 3.19 image running as a non-root user, suitable for execution inside sandbox pods.\n83: \n84: #### Scenario: Builder stage compiles picod binary\n85: - **GIVEN** `docker/Dockerfile.picod` is invoked with the repository root as build context\n86: - **WHEN** the builder stage runs `go build`\n87: - **THEN** it SHALL compile `./cmd/picod` with `CGO_ENABLED=0` and produce a static Linux binary\n88: \n89: #### Scenario: Runtime stage uses Alpine 3.19\n90: - **GIVEN** the runtime stage in `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n91: - **WHEN** the base image is inspected\n92: - **THEN** it SHALL be `alpine:3.19` (or a digest-pinned equivalent)\n93: \n94: #### Scenario: Non-root user is configured\n95: - **GIVEN** the runtime stage\n96: - **WHEN** the image is built\n97: - **THEN** it SHALL create a non-root user (UID ≥ 1000) and set it as the active user via `USER`\n98: \n99: #### Scenario: Entrypoint runs the picod binary\n100: - **GIVEN** a container launched from the built image\n101: - **WHEN** the container starts\n102: - **THEN** it SHALL execute the `picod` binary (via `ENTRYPOINT` or `CMD`)\n103: \n104: ### Requirement: Build context and reproducibility\n105: \n106: All three Dockerfiles SHALL use the repository root as build context and produce deterministic, minimal images suitable for production deployment.\n107: \n108: #### Scenario: Build context includes Go module files\n109: - **GIVEN** `docker build -f docker/Dockerfile .` is run from the repository root\n110: - **WHEN** the builder stage resolves dependencies\n111: - **THEN** `go.mod` and `go.sum` SHALL be available for `go mod download` before source code is copied (layer caching optimization)\n112: \n113: #### Scenario: No unnecessary files in runtime image\n114: - **GIVEN** a built image from any of the three Dockerfiles\n115: - **WHEN** the image filesystem is inspected\n116: - **THEN** it SHALL NOT contain Go source code, build caches, or the Go toolchain — only the compiled binary, Alpine base packages, and the non-root user home directory\n117: \n118: #### Scenario: Image builds succeed from clean checkout\n119: - **GIVEN** a clean clone of the repository at the correct commit\n120: - **WHEN** `docker build -f docker/Dockerfile -t workloadmanager:test .` is executed\n121: - **THEN** the build SHALL complete with exit code 0 and produce a valid image\n122: \n123: ### Requirement: Docker build output integrity\n124: \n125: Each built image SHALL contain a working binary that starts and responds to its health endpoint (where applicable).\n126: \n127: #### Scenario: Workload Manager image responds to /health\n128: - **GIVEN** a container running from the Workload Manager image with default configuration\n129: - **WHEN** an HTTP GET request is sent to `http://localhost:8080/health`\n130: - **THEN** the response SHALL return HTTP 200 OK\n131: \n132: #### Scenario: Router image starts without root privileges\n133: - **GIVEN** a container running from the Router image\n134: - **WHEN** the container's effective UID is inspected\n135: - **THEN** it SHALL be 1000 (the `router` user), not 0 (root)\n136: \n137: #### Scenario: PicoD image starts without root privileges\n138: - **GIVEN** a container running from the PicoD image\n139: - **WHEN** the container's effective UID is inspected\n140: - **THEN** it SHALL be ≥ 1000 (non-root user), not 0 (root)\n141: \n142: ---\n143: \n144: ## File Changes\n145: \n146: | Action | File | Description |\n147: |--------|------|-------------|\n148: | Create | `docker/Dockerfile` | Multi-stage build for Workload Manager (Go builder → Alpine 3.19, non-root `apiserver`) |\n149: | Create | `docker/Dockerfile.router` | Multi-stage build for Router (Go builder → Alpine 3.19, non-root `router`) |\n150: | Create | `docker/Dockerfile.picod` | Multi-stage build for PicoD daemon (Go builder → Alpine 3.19, non-root user) |\n151: | Create | `docker/.dockerignore` | Exclude `.git`, `test/`, `sdk-python/`, `docs/`, and other non-build artifacts from Docker context |\n\n(End of file - total 151 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-032: Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (3 images) — Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** `docker`\n- **Language:** Dockerfile\n- **Size:** S\n- **Base specs:** `deployment/spec.md` (Requirement: Docker images for core binaries)\n\n## Delta Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Workload Manager Dockerfile (multi-stage)\n\nThe system SHALL provide `docker/Dockerfile` that builds the Workload Manager binary via a multi-stage Docker build: a Go builder stage compiles `cmd/workloadmanager` with `CGO_ENABLED=0`, and a minimal runtime stage copies the binary into an Alpine 3.19 image running as non-root user `apiserver` (UID 1000), exposing port 8080.\n\n#### Scenario: Builder stage uses Go toolchain\n- **GIVEN** `docker/Dockerfile` is invoked with the repository root as build context\n- **WHEN** the first (builder) stage is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL use a Go base image (e.g. `golang:1.25-alpine`) and set `CGO_ENABLED=0` in the build environment\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-032/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775878517743,"end":1775878517751}}}}
