{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775878541765,"sessionID":"ses_285647e18ffeoctb678uOjeElq","part":{"id":"prt_d7a9c11c2001tdtAA4OVKVDUvi","messageID":"msg_d7a9c04b90019xTBzQPUbmH6tW","sessionID":"ses_285647e18ffeoctb678uOjeElq","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775878720454,"sessionID":"ses_285647e18ffeoctb678uOjeElq","part":{"id":"prt_d7a9c17cb0015H1y63ZTqhXGwO","messageID":"msg_d7a9c04b90019xTBzQPUbmH6tW","sessionID":"ses_285647e18ffeoctb678uOjeElq","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_453cd393e9fd449ba518c9c5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-034: CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 workflows) — Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** `.github`\n- **Language:** YAML\n- **Size:** L\n- **Base specs:** (No directly matching specs)\n\n## Scope\n\nThis delta spec covers the creation of 12 GitHub Actions workflow files under `.github/workflows/` that provide a complete CI/CD pipeline for the AgentCube project. The workflows SHALL cover PR build verification, Go linting, test coverage, E2E testing on Kind, code generation drift checks, copyright/spelling checks, Python SDK tests and linting, multi-architecture release image publication, Dify plugin publishing, and automated workflow approval for repeat contributors. All workflows SHALL use `dorny/paths-filter@v3` for path-based conditional execution where applicable, and SHALL consume Makefile targets defined in AR-033 without modifying any existing source code, Dockerfiles, or Helm charts.\n\n---\n\n## Workflow 1: main.yml — Agentcube CI Workflow\n\n### Requirement: Docker build on PR to main/release-*\n\nThe system SHALL provide `.github/workflows/main.yml` that builds the Workload Manager Docker image on pull requests targeting `main` or `release-*` branches.\n\n#### Scenario: PR to main triggers docker build\n- **GIVEN** a pull request targeting the `main` branch\n- **WHEN** the `Agentcube CI Workflow` job runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL checkout the repository, set up Docker Buildx, verify `docker`/`buildx` versions, and run `make docker-build`\n\n#### Scenario: PR to release-* triggers docker build\n- **GIVEN** a pull request targeting a `release-*` branch\n- **WHEN** the workflow is triggered\n- **THEN** it SHALL run `make docker-build` with the same steps as for `main`\n\n#### Scenario: PR to feature branch does NOT trigger workflow\n- **GIVEN** a pull request targeting a `feature/*` branch\n- **WHEN** the PR is opened\n- **THEN** the `main.yml` workflow SHALL NOT be triggered\n\n#### Scenario: Docker build failure fails the check\n- **GIVEN** the Dockerfile contains a syntax error\n- **WHEN** `make docker-build` executes in the workflow\n- **THEN** the workflow job SHALL fail with a non-zero exit code\n\n---\n\n## Workflow 2: lint.yml — Go Lint\n\n### Requirement: Path-filtered Go lint on PR\n\nThe system SHALL provide `.github/workflows/lint.yml` that runs `make lint` (golangci-lint) when Go-related paths change on pull requests to `main` or `release-*`.\n\n#### Scenario: Go file changes trigger lint\n- **GIVEN** a pull request and path filter `lint` matches `**/*.go`\n- **WHEN** the Lint workflow runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL use Go `1.24` and execute `make lint`\n\n#### Scenario: go.mod changes trigger lint\n- **GIVEN** a pull request modifies `go.mod` or `go.sum`\n- **WHEN** the path filter `lint` is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL match and the Lint workflow SHALL run\n\n#### Scenario: .golangci.yml changes trigger lint\n- **GIVEN** a pull request modifies `.golangci.yml`\n- **WHEN** the path filter `lint` is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL match (`.golangci.yml` is in the filter paths) and the Lint workflow SHALL run\n\n#### Scenario: Workflow file changes trigger lint\n- **GIVEN** a pull request modifies `.github/workflows/lint.yml`\n- **WHEN** the path filter `lint` is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL match and the Lint workflow SHALL run\n\n#### Scenario: No Go changes skip lint\n- **GIVEN** a pull request only modifies `docs/README.md`\n- **WHEN** the path filter `lint` is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL NOT match and the Lint workflow SHALL skip the lint job\n\n#### Scenario: Lint failure fails the check\n- **GIVEN** Go source code contains a golangci-lint violation\n- **WHEN** `make lint` executes\n- **THEN** the workflow job SHALL fail with a non-zero exit code\n\n---\n\n## Workflow 3: test-coverage.yml — Test Coverage\n\n### Requirement: Race-enabled coverage tests on PR/merge_group\n\nThe system SHALL provide `.github/workflows/test-coverage.yml` that runs race-enabled coverage tests on `pkg/...` for qualifying pull requests and merge groups, with optional Codecov upload.\n\n#### Scenario: Coverage test on PR\n- **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` and path filter `coverage` matches\n- **WHEN** the Test Coverage job runs with Go `1.24`\n- **THEN** it SHALL execute `go test -race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/... ./pkg/...`\n\n#### Scenario: Coverage test on merge_group\n- **GIVEN** a `merge_group` event and path filter `coverage` matches\n- **WHEN** the Test Coverage job runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL execute the same coverage command as for PR\n\n#### Scenario: Coverage artifact upload\n- **GIVEN** the coverage test completes successfully\n- **WHEN** the post-test step runs\n- **THEN** `coverage.out` SHALL be uploaded as a workflow artifact\n\n#### Scenario: Optional Codecov upload\n- **GIVEN** the `CODECOV_TOKEN` secret is configured and passed via `workflow_call`\n- **WHEN** the coverage job completes\n- **THEN** it SHALL upload the coverage report to Codecov via `codecov/codecov-action`\n\n#### Scenario: Codecov upload skipped when token absent\n- **GIVEN** the `CODECOV_TOKEN` secret is not configured\n- **WHEN** the coverage job completes\n- **THEN** the Codecov upload step SHALL be skipped without failing the workflow\n\n#### Scenario: Coverage path filter excludes docs/media\n- **GIVEN** a pull request only modifies `*.md`, `*.svg`, or `*.png` files\n- **WHEN** the path filter `coverage` is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL NOT match and the coverage job SHALL be skipped\n\n#### Scenario: Free disk space step\n- **GIVEN** the runner has limited disk space\n- **WHEN** the coverage job starts\n- **THEN** it SHALL run a `free-disk-space` step to ensure sufficient space for coverage data\n\n---\n\n## Workflow 4: e2e.yml — E2E Tests\n\n### Requirement: E2E testing on Kind cluster\n\nThe system SHALL provide `.github/workflows/e2e.yml` that runs `make e2e` in CI using a Kind-capable Ubuntu runner, capturing logs on failure.\n\n#### Scenario: E2E job on PR to main\n- **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*`\n- **WHEN** the E2E workflow runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL set `ARTIFACTS_PATH=${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`\n\n#### Scenario: Kind installation\n- **GIVEN** the E2E workflow is running\n- **WHEN** the Kind setup step executes\n- **THEN** it SHALL install Kind tool `v0.30.0` with `install_only: true`\n\n#### Scenario: E2E test execution\n- **GIVEN** the Kind cluster is ready\n- **WHEN** the E2E step runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL execute `make e2e` with Go `1.23`\n\n#### Scenario: E2E failure uploads logs\n- **GIVEN** `make e2e` fails\n- **WHEN** the workflow reaches the post-test step\n- **THEN** it SHALL upload the `e2e-logs` directory as a workflow artifact\n\n#### Scenario: E2E cleanup always runs\n- **GIVEN** the E2E workflow completes (pass or fail)\n- **WHEN** the cleanup step executes\n- **THEN** it SHALL always run `make e2e-clean`\n\n#### Scenario: E2E uses ubuntu runner\n- **GIVEN** the E2E workflow is triggered\n- **WHEN** the job runner is selected\n- **THEN** it SHALL use an Ubuntu runner with Kind capability\n\n---\n\n## Workflow 5: codegen-check.yml — Codegen Check\n\n### Requirement: Code generation drift detection\n\nThe system SHALL provide `.github/workflows/codegen-check.yml` that verifies generated artifacts match `make gen-all` when API, hack, workflow, or Makefile inputs change.\n\n#### Scenario: API changes trigger codegen check\n- **GIVEN** a pull request modifies files under `pkg/apis/**`\n- **WHEN** the path filter `codegen` is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL match and the Codegen Check workflow SHALL run\n\n#### Scenario: Hack directory changes trigger codegen check\n- **GIVEN** a pull request modifies files under `hack/**`\n- **WHEN** the path filter `codegen` is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL match and the Codegen Check workflow SHALL run\n\n#### Scenario: Workflow changes trigger codegen check\n- **GIVEN** a pull request modifies files under `.github/workflows/**`\n- **WHEN** the path filter `codegen` is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL match and the Codegen Check workflow SHALL run\n\n#### Scenario: Makefile changes trigger codegen check\n- **GIVEN** a pull request modifies the `Makefile`\n- **WHEN** the path filter `codegen` is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL match and the Codegen Check workflow SHALL run\n\n#### Scenario: Codegen check uses Go 1.24.4\n- **GIVEN** the Codegen Check workflow runs\n- **WHEN** Go is set up\n- **THEN** it SHALL use version `1.24.4`\n\n#### Scenario: Gen-check runs gen-all and diff\n- **GIVEN** the codegen check job is executing\n- **WHEN** the check step runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL execute `make gen-check` (which runs `gen-all` followed by `git diff --exit-code`)\n\n#### Scenario: Generated code drift fails the check\n- **GIVEN** generated files are out of sync with source (e.g., CRD changed but not regenerated)\n- **WHEN** `make gen-check` executes\n- **THEN** `git diff --exit-code` SHALL detect the difference and the workflow SHALL fail\n\n---\n\n## Workflow 6: copyright-check.yml — Copyright Check\n\n### Requirement: Copyright header verification\n\nThe system SHALL provide `.github/workflows/copyright-check.yml` that ensures `make gen-copyright` produces no git diff when applicable files change.\n\n#### Scenario: Source file changes trigger copyright check\n- **GIVEN** a pull request modifies a Go source file\n- **WHEN** the path filter `copyright` is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL match (Go files are not in the exclusion list) and the Copyright Check workflow SHALL run\n\n#### Scenario: Markdown changes skip copyright check\n- **GIVEN** a pull request only modifies `*.md` files\n- **WHEN** the path filter `copyright` is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL NOT match (`*.md` is excluded) and the workflow SHALL skip\n\n#### Scenario: SVG/PNG changes skip copyright check\n- **GIVEN** a pull request only modifies `*.svg` or `*.png` files\n- **WHEN** the path filter `copyright` is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL NOT match and the workflow SHALL skip\n\n#### Scenario: Docs directory changes skip copyright check\n- **GIVEN** a pull request only modifies files under `docs/**`\n- **WHEN** the path filter `copyright` is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL NOT match and the workflow SHALL skip\n\n#### Scenario: .github directory changes skip copyright check\n- **GIVEN** a pull request only modifies files under `.github/**`\n- **WHEN** the path filter `copyright` is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL NOT match and the workflow SHALL skip\n\n#### Scenario: Copyright check installs moreutils\n- **GIVEN** the copyright check job is running\n- **WHEN** the setup step executes\n- **THEN** it SHALL install `moreutils` (providing `sponge`) via `apt-get`\n\n#### Scenario: Copyright gen produces no diff\n- **GIVEN** all source files have correct copyright headers\n- **WHEN** `make gen-copyright` runs followed by `git diff --exit-code`\n- **THEN** the diff SHALL be empty and the workflow SHALL pass\n\n#### Scenario: Missing copyright header fails the check\n- **GIVEN** a new source file lacks the required copyright header\n- **WHEN** `make gen-copyright` runs followed by `git diff --exit-code`\n- **THEN** the diff SHALL detect the added header and the workflow SHALL fail\n\n---\n\n## Workflow 7: codespell.yml — Codespell\n\n### Requirement: Spelling check on PR\n\nThe system SHALL provide `.github/workflows/codespell.yml` that runs codespell on the repository for pull requests to `main` or `release-*`, temporarily moving files that cause false positives.\n\n#### Scenario: Codespell runs on PR to main\n- **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*`\n- **WHEN** the Codespell workflow runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL checkout the repository and install codespell via `pip install codespell`\n\n#### Scenario: False-positive files are temporarily moved\n- **GIVEN** the codespell job is about to run\n- **WHEN** the pre-check step executes\n- **THEN** it SHALL back up and remove `pyproject.toml`, `package-lock.json`, `package.json` from the repo root (and nested copies per `find`)\n\n#### Scenario: Codespell invocation with skip patterns\n- **GIVEN** false-positive files have been moved\n- **WHEN** codespell runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL use `--check-filenames`, specified `--skip` globs, and `--ignore-words-list fo,nam,te,notin,NotIn` on the `.` directory\n\n#### Scenario: Files are restored after codespell\n- **GIVEN** codespell has completed (pass or fail)\n- **WHEN** the post-check step executes\n- **THEN** it SHALL restore all backed-up files to their original locations\n\n#### Scenario: Spelling error fails the check\n- **GIVEN** a source file contains a misspelled word not in the ignore list\n- **WHEN** codespell runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL report the error and the workflow SHALL fail\n\n---\n\n## Workflow 8: python-sdk-tests.yml — Python SDK Tests\n\n### Requirement: Python SDK unit tests on path change\n\nThe system SHALL provide `.github/workflows/python-sdk-tests.yml` that runs pytest for the SDK when `sdk-python/**` changes.\n\n#### Scenario: SDK file changes trigger tests\n- **GIVEN** a pull request modifies files under `sdk-python/**`\n- **WHEN** the path filter `sdk` is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL match and the Python SDK Tests workflow SHALL run\n\n#### Scenario: Python 3.12 is used\n- **GIVEN** the Python SDK Tests job is running\n- **WHEN** Python is set up\n- **THEN** it SHALL use version `3.12`\n\n#### Scenario: Editable install\n- **GIVEN** the Python SDK Tests job is in the `sdk-python/` working directory\n- **WHEN** the setup step executes\n- **THEN** it SHALL run `pip install -e .`\n\n#### Scenario: Pytest execution\n- **GIVEN** the SDK is installed in editable mode\n- **WHEN** the test step runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL execute `python -m pytest tests/ -v`\n\n#### Scenario: SDK test failure fails the check\n- **GIVEN** a Python SDK test is failing\n- **WHEN** `python -m pytest tests/ -v` executes\n- **THEN** the workflow job SHALL fail with a non-zero exit code\n\n#### Scenario: No SDK changes skip tests\n- **GIVEN** a pull request only modifies Go source files\n- **WHEN** the path filter `sdk` is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL NOT match and the Python SDK Tests workflow SHALL skip\n\n---\n\n## Workflow 9: python-lint.yml — Python Lint\n\n### Requirement: Python lint with Ruff\n\nThe system SHALL provide `.github/workflows/python-lint.yml` that runs Ruff from repository root using `pyproject.toml` when Python-touching paths change.\n\n#### Scenario: CLI code changes trigger Python lint\n- **GIVEN** a pull request modifies files under `cmd/cli/**`\n- **WHEN** the path filter `python` is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL match and the Python Lint workflow SHALL run\n\n#### Scenario: SDK changes trigger Python lint\n- **GIVEN** a pull request modifies files under `sdk-python/**`\n- **WHEN** the path filter `python` is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL match and the Python Lint workflow SHALL run\n\n#### Scenario: Example code changes trigger Python lint\n- **GIVEN** a pull request modifies files under `example/**`\n- **WHEN** the path filter `python` is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL match and the Python Lint workflow SHALL run\n\n#### Scenario: Test Python files trigger lint\n- **GIVEN** a pull request modifies files matching `test/**/*.py`\n- **WHEN** the path filter `python` is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL match and the Python Lint workflow SHALL run\n\n#### Scenario: pyproject.toml changes trigger lint\n- **GIVEN** a pull request modifies `pyproject.toml`\n- **WHEN** the path filter `python` is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL match and the Python Lint workflow SHALL run\n\n#### Scenario: Python lint uses Python 3.10\n- **GIVEN** the Python Lint job is running\n- **WHEN** Python is set up\n- **THEN** it SHALL use version `3.10`\n\n#### Scenario: Ruff check execution\n- **GIVEN** Python is set up and ruff is installed\n- **WHEN** the lint step runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL execute `python3 -m ruff check . --config pyproject.toml`\n\n#### Scenario: Ruff violation fails the check\n- **GIVEN** a Python file contains a Ruff-detectable issue\n- **WHEN** `ruff check . --config pyproject.toml` executes\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL fail with a non-zero exit code\n\n---\n\n## Workflow 10: build-push-release.yml — Build and Push Release Images\n\n### Requirement: Multi-architecture release image publication\n\nThe system SHALL provide `.github/workflows/build-push-release.yml` that builds and pushes multi-architecture images for workloadmanager, router, and picod to GitHub Container Registry on pushes to `main` and on semantic version tags.\n\n#### Scenario: Push to main builds latest images\n- **GIVEN** a push event to the `main` branch\n- **WHEN** the workflow is triggered\n- **THEN** `TAG` SHALL be set to `latest` and multi-arch images SHALL be built and pushed\n\n#### Scenario: Semantic version tag builds tagged images\n- **GIVEN** a push event with `github.ref_type` equal to `tag` matching `v*.*.*` or `v*.*.*-*`\n- **WHEN** the workflow is triggered\n- **THEN** `TAG` SHALL be set to `github.ref_name` (e.g., `v0.1.0`) and images SHALL be tagged accordingly\n\n#### Scenario: GHCR login\n- **GIVEN** the release build job is running\n- **WHEN** the registry login step executes\n- **THEN** it SHALL log in to `ghcr.io` using `GITHUB_TOKEN`\n\n#### Scenario: Image registry is set correctly\n- **GIVEN** the release build job is running\n- **WHEN** the build steps execute\n- **THEN** `IMAGE_REGISTRY` SHALL be set to `ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}`\n\n#### Scenario: Workloadmanager image is built and pushed\n- **GIVEN** the release workflow is running\n- **WHEN** the workloadmanager build step executes\n- **THEN** it SHALL run `make docker-buildx-push-workloadmanager` with the correct `IMAGE_REGISTRY` and `WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE`\n\n#### Scenario: Router image is built and pushed\n- **GIVEN** the release workflow is running\n- **WHEN** the router build step executes\n- **THEN** it SHALL run `make docker-buildx-push-router` with the correct `IMAGE_REGISTRY` and `ROUTER_IMAGE`\n\n#### Scenario: Picod image is built and pushed\n- **GIVEN** the release workflow is running\n- **WHEN** the picod build step executes\n- **THEN** it SHALL run `make docker-buildx-push-picod` with the correct `IMAGE_REGISTRY` and `PICOD_IMAGE`\n\n#### Scenario: Non-matching tag does NOT trigger release\n- **GIVEN** a push event with a tag that does NOT match semantic versioning (e.g., `docs-update`)\n- **WHEN** the workflow trigger is evaluated\n- **THEN** the `build-push-release.yml` workflow SHALL NOT be triggered\n\n#### Scenario: Feature branch push does NOT trigger release\n- **GIVEN** a push to a `feature/*` branch\n- **WHEN** the workflow trigger is evaluated\n- **THEN** the `build-push-release.yml` workflow SHALL NOT be triggered\n\n---\n\n## Workflow 11: dify-plugin-publish.yml — Dify Plugin Publish\n\n### Requirement: Dify plugin packaging and PR submission\n\nThe system SHALL provide `.github/workflows/dify-plugin-publish.yml` that packages a Dify plugin and automatically submits a PR to the `langgenius/dify-plugins` repository when a `dify-plugin/v*` tag is pushed.\n\n#### Scenario: Dify plugin tag triggers publish\n- **GIVEN** a push event with tag matching `dify-plugin/v*`\n- **WHEN** the workflow is triggered\n- **THEN** it SHALL checkout the repository and package the Dify plugin\n\n#### Scenario: Plugin packaging\n- **GIVEN** the dify-plugin-publish workflow is running\n- **WHEN** the packaging step executes\n- **THEN** it SHALL create a distributable plugin archive from the `dify-plugin/` directory\n\n#### Scenario: PR submission to langgenius/dify-plugins\n- **GIVEN** the plugin is packaged\n- **WHEN** the PR submission step executes\n- **THEN** it SHALL use `peter-evans/create-pull-request` to create a PR against `langgenius/dify-plugins`\n\n#### Scenario: PLUGIN_ACTION secret is used for authentication\n- **GIVEN** the PR submission step requires cross-repo access\n- **WHEN** the step executes\n- **THEN** it SHALL use the `PLUGIN_ACTION` secret for authentication\n\n#### Scenario: Non-dify-plugin tag does NOT trigger workflow\n- **GIVEN** a push event with tag `v0.1.0` (not matching `dify-plugin/v*`)\n- **WHEN** the workflow trigger is evaluated\n- **THEN** the `dify-plugin-publish.yml` workflow SHALL NOT be triggered\n\n---\n\n## Workflow 12: workflows-approve.yml — Approve Workflows\n\n### Requirement: Automated workflow approval for repeat contributors\n\nThe system SHALL provide `.github/workflows/workflows-approve.yml` that optionally approves pending workflow runs for pull requests from repeat contributors or those labeled `ok-to-test`.\n\n#### Scenario: pull_request_target on labeled event\n- **GIVEN** a `pull_request_target` event on `main` or `release-*` with `labeled` or `synchronize` type\n- **WHEN** the workflow is triggered\n- **THEN** it SHALL evaluate the contributor's PR history\n\n#### Scenario: Repeat contributor is auto-approved\n- **GIVEN** the PR author has more than one PR in the repository\n- **WHEN** the approval step executes\n- **THEN** it SHALL list workflow runs for the head SHA with `status: action_required` and call `approveWorkflowRun` for each\n\n#### Scenario: ok-to-test label triggers approval\n- **GIVEN** the PR has the `ok-to-test` label (regardless of contributor history)\n- **WHEN** the approval step executes\n- **THEN** it SHALL approve all pending workflow runs for the PR\n\n#### Scenario: First-time contributor without label is NOT approved\n- **GIVEN** the PR author has only one PR and the PR does NOT have the `ok-to-test` label\n- **WHEN** the approval step evaluates\n- **THEN** it SHALL NOT approve any workflow runs\n\n#### Scenario: No action_required runs to approve\n- **GIVEN** all workflow runs for the head SHA have already started or completed\n- **WHEN** the approval step lists runs with `status: action_required`\n- **THEN** the list SHALL be empty and the step SHALL succeed without action\n\n---\n\n## Workflow Trigger Matrix\n\n### Requirement: Workflow trigger correctness\n\nEach workflow SHALL be triggered only by the events specified in the trigger matrix.\n\n#### Scenario: PR to main triggers 9 workflows\n- **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` with changes across all paths\n- **WHEN** the PR is opened\n- **THEN** the following workflows SHALL be triggered: `main.yml`, `lint.yml`, `test-coverage.yml`, `e2e.yml`, `codegen-check.yml`, `copyright-check.yml`, `codespell.yml`, `python-sdk-tests.yml`, `python-lint.yml`\n\n#### Scenario: Push to main triggers release workflow\n- **GIVEN** a push to `main`\n- **WHEN** the push event is processed\n- **THEN** only `build-push-release.yml` SHALL be triggered (with `TAG=latest`)\n\n#### Scenario: Semantic version tag triggers release workflow\n- **GIVEN** a push of tag `v0.2.0`\n- **WHEN** the push event is processed\n- **THEN** only `build-push-release.yml` SHALL be triggered (with `TAG=v0.2.0`)\n\n#### Scenario: Dify plugin tag triggers plugin publish\n- **GIVEN** a push of tag `dify-plugin/v1.0.0`\n- **WHEN** the push event is processed\n- **THEN** only `dify-plugin-publish.yml` SHALL be triggered\n\n#### Scenario: PR labeled ok-to-test triggers approval\n- **GIVEN** a PR to `main` receives the `ok-to-test` label\n- **WHEN** the `labeled` event fires\n- **THEN** `workflows-approve.yml` SHALL be triggered\n\n---\n\n## Path Filter Configuration\n\n### Requirement: dorny/paths-filter usage\n\nAll workflows that use conditional path-based execution SHALL use `dorny/paths-filter@v3` with correctly configured path patterns.\n\n#### Scenario: lint filter matches Go files\n- **GIVEN** the `lint.yml` workflow defines filter `lint`\n- **WHEN** the filter paths are inspected\n- **THEN** they SHALL include `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, `.github/workflows/lint.yml`\n\n#### Scenario: coverage filter excludes docs/media\n- **GIVEN** the `test-coverage.yml` workflow defines filter `coverage`\n- **WHEN** the filter paths are inspected\n- **THEN** they SHALL match `**` with negative patterns excluding `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`\n\n#### Scenario: codegen filter matches generation inputs\n- **GIVEN** the `codegen-check.yml` workflow defines filter `codegen`\n- **WHEN** the filter paths are inspected\n- **THEN** they SHALL include `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, `Makefile`\n\n#### Scenario: copyright filter excludes non-code files\n- **GIVEN** the `copyright-check.yml` workflow defines filter `copyright`\n- **WHEN** the filter paths are inspected\n- **THEN** they SHALL match all files except `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`, `docs/**`, `.github/**`\n\n#### Scenario: sdk filter matches Python SDK\n- **GIVEN** the `python-sdk-tests.yml` workflow defines filter `sdk`\n- **WHEN** the filter paths are inspected\n- **THEN** they SHALL include `sdk-python/**`\n\n#### Scenario: python filter matches all Python paths\n- **GIVEN** the `python-lint.yml` workflow defines filter `python`\n- **WHEN** the filter paths are inspected\n- **THEN** they SHALL include `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py`, `pyproject.toml`\n\n---\n\n## Security\n\n### Requirement: Secret management and permission minimization\n\nWorkflows SHALL use secrets and permissions following the principle of least privilege.\n\n#### Scenario: GITHUB_TOKEN used only for registry login\n- **GIVEN** the `build-push-release.yml` workflow runs\n- **WHEN** the GHCR login step executes\n- **THEN** it SHALL use `GITHUB_TOKEN` with only the permissions required for container registry write access\n\n#### Scenario: CODECOV_TOKEN is optional\n- **GIVEN** the `test-coverage.yml` workflow runs\n- **WHEN** the Codecov upload step is evaluated\n- **THEN** it SHALL check for the presence of `CODECOV_TOKEN` and skip gracefully if absent\n\n#### Scenario: PLUGIN_ACTION secret for cross-repo access\n- **GIVEN** the `dify-plugin-publish.yml` workflow runs\n- **WHEN** the PR creation step executes\n- **THEN** it SHALL use `PLUGIN_ACTION` secret for authentication to the external `langgenius/dify-plugins` repository\n\n#### Scenario: pull_request_target is NOT used for code execution\n- **GIVEN** the `workflows-approve.yml` workflow\n- **WHEN** the workflow is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL use `pull_request_target` ONLY for the approval action (which does not execute repository code), not for any step that checks out or runs repository code\n\n---\n\n## File Changes\n\n| Action | File | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| Create | `.github/workflows/main.yml` | Agentcube CI Workflow: Docker build on PR to main/release-* |\n| Create | `.github/workflows/lint.yml` | Go Lint: path-filtered golangci-lint on Go file changes |\n| Create | `.github/workflows/test-coverage.yml` | Test Coverage: race-enabled coverage tests with optional Codecov upload |\n| Create | `.github/workflows/e2e.yml` | E2E Tests: Kind-based E2E testing with log artifact upload on failure |\n| Create | `.github/workflows/codegen-check.yml` | Codegen Check: detect drift between generated artifacts and source |\n| Create | `.github/workflows/copyright-check.yml` | Copyright Check: verify copyright headers via make gen-copyright |\n| Create | `.github/workflows/codespell.yml` | Codespell: spelling check with false-positive file handling |\n| Create | `.github/workflows/python-sdk-tests.yml` | Python SDK Tests: pytest on sdk-python changes |\n| Create | `.github/workflows/python-lint.yml` | Python Lint: Ruff check on Python path changes |\n| Create | `.github/workflows/build-push-release.yml` | Build and Push Release: multi-arch images to GHCR on main push or version tag |\n| Create | `.github/workflows/dify-plugin-publish.yml` | Dify Plugin Publish: package plugin and PR to langgenius/dify-plugins |\n| Create | `.github/workflows/workflows-approve.yml` | Approve Workflows: auto-approve pending runs for repeat contributors |\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-034/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-034/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-034/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775878720433,"end":1775878720451}}}}
